How to Use Referrals for High Quality, Low Cost Leads

*“Have you been to the new cafe on main street? It’s really good\!”*

*“I know a good plumber. He’ll find and fix that leak--no problem.”*

These are simple, good ol’ fashioned word-of-mouth referrals.

Word-of-mouth referrals are one of the most basic and powerful forms of advertising, simply because it gives you instant credibility with your prospects. People will trust their friends much sooner than your ad on Facebook. If you can get your customers talking about you to their friends, you know you’re on the right track.

However, it’s so simple we sometimes take it for granted, not using referrals to their fullest potential..

You can capitalize on them by implementing a simple system for collection referrals. Here are some ideas:

- **Referral rewards**: Offer a discount, credit or outright cash, to customers who bring in new customers.  
- **Partnering:** Work with someone serving the same clientele. For example, a mechanic could partner with the local parts store.  
- **Simply ask:** Satisfied customers are more than happy to refer you to friends. But, just like you, they have many things on their mind and simply need reminded.

Most importantly, be intentional about asking for referrals. If you assume that referrals will “just come”, you will ignore the best leads in the market. However, if you create an effective referral system, you can gain access to high quality leads at a much lower cost.
